  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ICEE (FTC Abuja)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall aim of the project is the reduction of prevalence of blindness and visual impairment by 50% in FCT, Abuja through the provision of high quality comprehensive eye care services by well trained and equitably distributed personnel working in well-equipped facilities with full community participation. 

The objectives include;
&#x2022; To ensure policy makers take ownership of the programme and its embedment in the overall health system.
&#x2022; To have in post adequate number of well trained and equitably distributed eye care personnel at all levels to meet the eye care needs of the people
&#x2022; To have in place required infrastructure and technology to enable the provision of good quality eye care services in at least 50% of the state.

The key project activities are Advocacy; programme management; human resource development; service delivery; Information Education &amp; Communication; Provision of infrastructure &amp; supply of equipment &amp; consumables and monitoring &amp; evaluation and service delivery

The project aims at contributing to the reduction of poverty by reducing avoidable blindness.</narrative>
  </description>
